%N A391373 The largest number with an arithmetic mean of divisors equal to n or 0 is there is no such number.
%C A391373 a(n) is the largest k such that sigma(k)/tau(k) = A000203(k)/A000005(k) = n.
%C A391373 Zeros occur if n is in A157847 (not in A157846).
%C A391373 a(n) is finite for all n since sigma(k) >= k+1 and tau(k) <= 2*sqrt(k) implies no qualifying k can exceed 4*n^2.
%F A391373 a(n) = max({k : sigma(k) = n*tau(k)} U {0}).
%e A391373 a(2) = 3 because 3 is the largest k that satisfies sigma(k)/tau(k) = 2.
%e A391373 a(3) = 6 because 6 is the largest k that satisfies sigma(k)/tau(k) = 3.
%e A391373 a(5) = 0 because no k satisfies sigma(k)/tau(k) = 5.
%o A391373 (Python)
%o A391373 from sympy import divisor_count, divisor_sigma
%o A391373 def a(n):
%o A391373     max_k = 0
%o A391373     for k in range(1, 4*n*n + 1):
%o A391373         if divisor_sigma(k) == n * divisor_count(k): max_k = k
%o A391373     return max_k
%o A391373 (PARI) a(n) = forstep(k=4*n^2+1, 1, -1, my(f=factor(k)); if (sigma(f)/numdiv(f) == n, return(k))); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Dec 08 2025
